This list musicology topics Musicology the scholarly study music person who studies music musicologist The word used narrow intermediate and broad senses the narrow sense musicology confined the music history Western culture the intermediate sense includes all relevant cultures and range musical forms styles genres and traditions but tends confined the humanities combination historical musicology ethnomusicology and the humanities systematic musicology philosophy theoretical sociology aesthetics the broad sense includes all musically relevant disciplines both humanities and sciences and all manifestations music all cultures also includes all systematic musicology including psychology biology and computing example Znamenny notation with socalled red marks Russia 1884 Thy Cross honour Lord and Thy holy Resurrection praise 